Lemma 4.1 (Vacancy Stress Concentration): If vacancies exist in the core proto-brick arrangement (i.e., the actual proto-brick count is less than the ideal closure count for that weaving tree order), then the topological stress concentration factor at the suture line I > 0. If no vacancies exist, I ≈ 0.

Proof (Constructive):

In an ideal closure (such as a 12³ hypercube), each proto-brick in the core forms perfectly saturated links with neighboring proto-bricks via its dangling link ports, and stress is uniformly distributed along the suture line.

When the core lacks m proto-brick units, asymmetric gaps appear in the link network around the missing positions. The proto-bricks on the suture line at the positions corresponding to these gaps must bear additional topological stress to maintain mechanical equilibrium of the overall configuration. This additional stress cannot be completely eliminated through uniform rearrangement because the vacancies break the discrete symmetry of the closure.

Therefore, I > 0 if and only if core vacancies exist. ■

