First, the geometrization of quantum statistics: by proving that the exchange operation of identical topological knots necessarily corresponds to an odd number of reconnection steps, whereas the identity operation corresponds to zero steps, the parity opposition enforces the Pauli exclusion principle. This derivation completely eliminates reliance on "antisymmetric wave functions" or the "spin-statistics theorem." The complete derivation of shell filling numbers 2n² has been explicitly marked as the boundary for subsequent work, without affecting the rigor of Pauli exclusion itself.

