With this, TDMU 2.31 has achieved rigorous formal closure at three levels: quantum statistics, nuclear structure, and condensed matter gauge fields. All derivations use only the pure combinatorial language of nodes, directed edges, reconnection steps, and dangling link ports, without introducing continuous spatial metrics, wave function assumptions, or preset Standard Model constants at any step. The unfinished parts of the theory have been honestly delimited as boundaries for independent supplements—this honesty itself is part of formal closure.

